Israeli Stocks: Fundtech, Pangaea Real Estate, Magic Software

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-06-15T15:18:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/israeli-stocks-fundtech-pangaea-real-estate-magic-software.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index dropped to the
lowest level since Sept. 19, declining 2.7 percent to 1,189.53
at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . Investors traded about 1.81
billion shekels ($530.4 million) in shares and convertible
securities.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Fundtech Ltd. (FNDT)   surged to the highest since
November 2007, rallying 16 percent to 69.47 shekels. The
provider of banking software said a multinational corporation
has expressed interest in acquiring the company. It also said
it’s in preliminary talks on a possible merger transaction with
a U.S. company.  Magic Software Enterprises Ltd. (MGIC)   rose to the
highest since June 6, advancing 1.2 percent to 16.40 shekels.
Lloyd’s and London Markets Insurance ISV, Total Objects, chose
the software developer’s iBolt integration platform.  Pangaea Real Estate Ltd. (PNGD)   increased the most since
June 6, jumping 6.6 percent to 0.835 shekel. The property
developer and partners including  Electra Real Estate Ltd. (ELCRE)   agreed to purchase land in Tel Aviv from Tnuva for 530
million shekels to build a residential and commercial project.
Electra rose less than 0.1 percent to 20.11 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
